# .fork-sync-ignore — upstream commits fork-sync must skip.
#
# One SHA per line, optional reason after whitespace.
# Blank lines and # comments allowed.
#
# See CLAUDE.md in pmin-mcpinfrastructure for the full convention. When an
# upstream commit is listed here, the weekly sync cron on mcp-server will
# silently skip it instead of tripping a merge conflict.
#
# Listed SHAs must exist in `upstream/main` — otherwise the sync script
# will log a warning and treat the entry as a no-op.

# --- mcp-google-ads: reject upstream OAuth reimplementation (2026-04-13) ---
# Upstream implemented their own OAuth proxy in googleads/mcp-google-ads#46
